===Etymology===
The etymology is uncertain; older forms are ''Madraspatan'', ''Madraspatanam'', and ''Madraspattinam'', the final element being from Sanskrit [[पत्तन]]{{fact}} (pattana) ‘village, city’. It is possible that ''Madras'' is from Arabic {{Arab|[[مدرسة]]}} (madrásah) ‘college’, from {{Arab|[[درس]]}} (dárasa) ‘to learn, to study’.

